This represents a significant 90% surge since FY 2019-20. Singh attributed this growth to the collaborative efforts of the Department of Defence Production, DPSUs, public sector manufacturers, and the private industry.
title: Defence output soars: Annual production in FY25 hits Rs 1.5 lakh crore, says Rajnath

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: US President Trump has reignited discussions on federal marijuana restrictions, hinting at potential policy changes. During a recent gathering, he acknowledged the need to re-evaluate the existing regulations. This comes nearly a year after he initially suggested easing access to regulated cannabis and granting states greater autonomy. While some advisors see cannabis reform as a boost for the upcoming midterms, others caution against potential legal and moral repercussions.
title: Make America Baked Again? Trump talks weed over dinner with donors

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Panic struck the Icon of the Seas when a water slide's glass panel shattered mid-ride, injuring a male guest. Water flooded the deck as passengers screamed for the ride to stop. Royal Caribbean is investigating the incident, and the slide is closed for the remainder of the cruise after the ship departed from Miami on August 2, 2023.
title: 'Stop the slide': Royal Caribbean water slide glass breaks mid-way - Watch

author: ABHAY
description: In a tragic incident in Delhi's Karawal Nagar, police are actively searching for a man named Pradeep, who is suspected of murdering his wife, Jaya Shri, and their two young daughters, aged five and seven. Preliminary investigations suggest that ongoing marital disputes may have been a contributing factor in this horrific crime.
title: Triple murder in Delhi: Man kills wife, daughters in Karawal Nagar; accused absconding

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Armenian Prime Minister Nikol Pashinyan and Azerbaijani President Ilham Aliyev have jointly endorsed Donald Trump for the Nobel Peace Prize. This follows a landmark peace agreement mediated by Trump between the two nations, ending decades of conflict. Both leaders lauded Trump's efforts at a White House signing, emphasizing his role in achieving the breakthrough.
title: Trump ‘nobel’ for Nobel: Now, Armenia and Azerbaijan back US President for peace prize

author: TOI CITY DESK
title: Watch: Chaos at Delhi airport as Air India delay angers passengers

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Delhi was severely affected by incessant heavy rains, leading to widespread waterlogging and traffic disruptions across key areas like Vasant Kunj and Connaught Place. The India Meteorological Department initially issued a red alert, which was later downgraded to yellow, forecasting continued thunderstorms until August 12. The city recorded significant rainfall, with Safdarjung reporting 78.7 mm.
title: Drowning Delhi: Flooded roads, stuck cars and soaked capital - heavy rains lash city

author: SHRIVATHSAN S
description: Chennai-born Nivethan Radhakrishnan, an ambidextrous spinner playing for Tasmania, is honing his skills at the MRF Academy in Chennai. Inspired by Ashwin and Lyon, the 22-year-old aims to enhance his consistency and variety. He is part of Cricket Australia's developmental squad, focusing on mastering both off-spin and leg-spin to excel in Australian domestic cricket.
title: 'I am a little bit like Ashwin': Ambidextrous Nivethan hopes to emulate Lyon

author: FAZAL KHAN
description: RP Singh cautioned that Mohammed Siraj needs workload management despite his impressive performance in England, similar to Jasprit Bumrah's situation. He advocated for monitoring workload in domestic cricket rather than international matches. Singh also supported Arshdeep Singh's inclusion in the team and believed Anshul Kamboj has potential despite a poor debut due to lack of rest.
title: 'Mohammed Siraj needs to be cautious about workload'

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Donald Trump is set to meet Vladimir Putin in Alaska on August 15, 2025, aiming to broker a peace deal to end the Ukraine war. Trump believes he has "a shot" at securing peace, hinting at possible territory swaps. The meeting follows a visit by Trump’s envoy to Moscow, though Russia dismissed a three-way summit with Zelenskyy.
title: Why are Trump, Putin meeting in Alaska and will Zelenskyy be present?

author: DWAIPAYAN DATTA
description: Chennai Super Kings are planning a significant rebuild after a disappointing IPL season, potentially releasing seasoned players like R Ashwin and Devon Conway to free up approximately Rs 34.45 cr for the upcoming auction. CSK aims to bolster their batting lineup with a top-order hitter, a strong Indian middle-order batsman, and a quality all-rounder.
title: IPL: CSK may free up purse to add firepower; Dhoni likely to play

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: An ongoing encounter in Jammu and Kashmir's Kulgam district, under Operation Akhal, has resulted in the death of two soldiers, confirmed by the Army on Saturday. The operation, initiated on August 1, has also led to the killing of two unidentified terrorists.
title: Operation Akhal enters day 9: Two soldiers killed in J&K's Kulgam

author: RAJ SHEKHAR JHA
description: Comedian Kapil Sharma is now under threat from the Lawrence Bishnoi syndicate due to his connection with Salman Khan. This follows a shooting at Sharma's restaurant in Canada, claimed by the Bishnoi gang. An audio clip reveals threats against those working with Khan, vowing violence, even murder, using AK-47s.
title: ‘Will kill anyone working with Salman Khan’: Kapil Sharma's café shooting

author: PRIYANGI AGARWAL
description: The Yamuna River in Delhi reached a seasonal high of 205.15 meters, nearing the danger level before receding. Despite the halt in rainfall, an expert cautioned vigilance due to past late monsoon floods. The flood helped improve water quality by flushing out toxins, highlighting the importance of river flows.
title: Delhi rains: Yamuna has brush with ‘danger’ for 2 hours; crosses 205.33m mark

author: ABHAY
description: In Delhi's Jangpura, Asif Qureshi, cousin of actress Huma Qureshi, was fatally stabbed following a parking dispute with brothers Ujjawal and Gautam. The altercation escalated after Qureshi asked Ujjawal to move his scooter, leading to a violent confrontation. Both brothers, known for their aggressive temper and prior history of altercations, have been arrested by the police.
title: Huma Qureshi cousin murdered: 'Accused brothers known for bad temper, picking fights'

author: PRADEEP GUPTA AND GEORGE MENDONCA
description: Recent incidents highlight the Marathi versus non-Marathi divide in Maharashtra. In Kalyan, MNS workers allegedly assaulted an idli vendor for derogatory remarks. A video from a local train shows a heated argument between two women over language preference. Police have not received formal complaints in either case. The incidents underscore existing tensions in the state.
title: Marathi vs non-Marathi row: MNS men assault idli vendor in Kalyan; heated spat erupts on train

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu declared Israel's aim to "free" Gaza from Hamas and establish a peaceful civilian government, excluding Hamas, the Palestinian Authority, or any terrorist organization. This statement follows the approval of a military plan involving control of Gaza City, sparking international criticism.
title: ‘Not to occupy but free Gaza’: Netanyahu defends Israel's military plans

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Ajinkya Rahane praised Jasprit Bumrah's transparent communication regarding his workload management for the England Test series. Bumrah's decision to play only three Tests, despite being a key player, demonstrated his commitment to the team's needs. Rahane advised the management to use Bumrah in shorter spells to ensure his availability for future series, highlighting his impact on England's 'Bazball' approach.
title: Rahane hails Bumrah's courage: 'Sometimes players convey message and get dropped'

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Pakistani cricketer Haider Ali has been arrested in Manchester on rape charges stemming from an alleged incident on July 23, 2025. Greater Manchester Police are investigating, and Ali has been released on bail. His young career so far has included the iconic India vs Pakistan match at the 2022 T20 World Cup but he was unable to make a mark in that contest.
title: Watch: When Pandya dismissed Haider Ali, Pakistani cricketer arrested on rape charges

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Matthew Hayden commented on Gautam Gambhir's heated exchange with the Oval pitch curator, Lee Fortis, during India's training session. Hayden acknowledged Gambhir's frustration with perceived restrictions but suggested he could have used better language. Greg Blewett echoed the sentiment, recalling similar frustrations and noting the language used wasn't ideal, despite India securing a series-levelling victory.
title: 'Could have used better language': Ex-Aussie star weighs in on Gambhir–curator clash

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Delhi and the NCR experienced heavy rainfall on Saturday, leading to flight delays and cancellations, with approximately 90 flights affected and several areas waterlogged. The IMD has forecast continued thunderstorms and rain throughout the day in the capital.
title: Heavy rain in Delhi-NCR: Flights delayed, roads waterlogged; IMD warns of more showers

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Ravichandran Ashwin cleverly addressed IPL trade rumours in a new video, engaging Rajasthan Royals skipper Sanju Samson in a humorous exchange about potential team switches. Ashwin joked about trading himself to stay in Kerala, while reports suggest Samson's unhappiness with RR and CSK's interest in signing him. This playful banter turns transfer speculation into lighthearted entertainment for fans.
title: Watch: Ashwin's cheeky take on IPL rumours leaves Samson, fans in splits

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Raksha Bandhan, a cherished Indian festival celebrating the sibling bond, falls on August 9, 2025. The festival emphasizes love, trust, and protection between siblings, marked by tying a rakhi. The article provides 50+ heartfelt messages and quotes to share with siblings, along with ideas to make the celebration extra special, whether near or far, fostering deeper connections.
title: Happy Raksha Bandhan 2025: Top 50 wishes, messages, and quotes; share with your siblings

author: TNN
description: Piyush Goyal asserted India's resilience, stating it won't bow down to anyone and will capitalize on global trade restructuring. He expressed confidence in India's economic strength and ability to find opportunities amidst crises like potential Trump tariffs. Goyal highlighted India's growing global recognition and attractiveness as a market, dismissing concerns about its economic status.
title: India won't bow down to anybody, says Piyush Goyal

author: PRATYUSH RAJ
description: Under Gautam Gambhir, India have played 15 Test matches, winning five and losing eight, including an embarrassing series defeat at home to New Zealand, their first in 12 years. His red-ball tactics have raised eyebrows; his rigidity in prioritising batting depth over balance, and his decision to keep Kuldeep Yadav on the bench, cost India a golden chance to bury the Bazballers once and for all. India did manage to draw the series, thanks to a spirited performance by the extraordinary skills of Mohammed Siraj, but they should have beaten toothless England.
title: WTC glory needs specialists, not stopgaps — Gambhir must rethink his approach

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: For their movie Saiyaara's ending, the filmmakers surprisingly consulted ChatGPT, an AI chatbot. The team was looking for a perfect balance between drama and realism. Although one of the AI-generated endings, a bittersweet parting at a train station, initially intrigued them, the filmmakers ultimately opted for a more culturally nuanced and emotionally resonant conclusion crafted by human writers.
title: ChatGPT's Saiyaara climax: Alternate ending revealed; very different from the original

author: TNN
description: In a tragic incident in Udaipur's Jindoli village, a woman, Mangi Gameti, and her mother-in-law, Pappa Bai, died after Mangi set herself on fire following a domestic dispute with her husband. The fire rapidly spread due to inflammable materials in the room, trapping both women.
title: Udaipur shocker: Woman, mother-in-law burnt alive after dispute

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Rumors swirl around Tom Brady's love life, linking him to both Kim Kardashian and Sofia Vergara. Sources suggest Kardashian is very interested in Brady, even making her feelings known at Jeff Bezos' wedding. However, Brady and Vergara were spotted dining together, sparking further speculation. While Vergara downplays the relationship as a casual fling, Kardashian reportedly hopes it ends soon.
title: Kim Kardashian ‘chases’ Tom Brady; 'She threw herself at him'; Sofia Vergara romance rumors swir

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: President Donald Trump announced a meeting with Russian President Vladimir Putin in Alaska on August 15, 2025, to discuss ending the ongoing war in Ukraine. This marks Putin's first visit to the US in a decade, signaling a potential shift in diplomatic efforts. Trump expressed optimism about brokering a peace deal, despite previous failed talks between Moscow and Kyiv.
title: Trump-Putin summit: Meeting set for next Friday in Alaska; to discuss ending Ukraine war

author: SACHIN PARASHAR
description: Amidst strained US-India relations due to trade disputes over Russian ties, PM Modi and President Putin reaffirmed their commitment to strengthening India-Russia relations. Modi expressed support for resolving the Russia-Ukraine conflict through diplomacy and invited Putin to India for the annual summit.
title: Amid escalation with US, PM Modi and Putin back India-Russia ties

author: TNN
description: In Bengaluru, a 55-year-old security guard confessed to murdering his 14-year-old nephew after an argument over money for a mobile game. Naga Prasad surrendered to police after a failed suicide attempt, leading to the discovery of the teenager's body in his rented room. Prasad admitted to slitting his nephew's throat due to his constant demands and arrogant behavior.
title: Bengaluru: Man slits throat of 14-year-old nephew over demand for gaming phone
